x4freetext: LANSCE/WNR facility,neutrons produced
in a    natural W spallation target driven by an
800-MeV proton beam
2.2 g of Tl oxide powder, 97.0% enriched in 203Tl,
in a polystyrene capsule, 2.3 cm dia and 0.8 mm thick
GEANIE spectrometer consisting of
11 Compton suppressed planar Ge detectors,
9 Compton suppressed coaxial Ge detectors,
and 6 unsuppressed coaxial Ge detectors, located
20.34 m from the WNR spallation target on the
60 deg - right flight path
Energy of incident neutrons determined
by time-of-flight method
Neutron flux monitored with fission chamber
using  235U and 238U foils
